This is the readme file for the test runner.

--------------------------------------------------------
usage:	ruby testrunner.rb [test_1 flag_1 ...]
	ruby testrunner.rb < args.in

where args.in uses this format:
file_1 halt_on_fail
file_2 halt_on_fail
...

--------------------------------------------------------
The test runner returns the following:
<test_suite>
	<test>
		<id>file_i</id>
		<input>test_input</input>
		<expected>expected_output</expected>
		<output>actual_output</output>
		<marks>marks_earned</marks>
		<status>Pass/Fail/Error</status>
	</test>
	...
<test_suite>


--------------------------------------------------------
The only requirements on the test files are that the first three lines are:
"marks\n\n"
"input\n\n"
"expected\n\n"
All remaining output (to stdout) is assumed to be the actual output from the 
test.
Currently, the output to stderr is not included in the results.

All imported files are found in the directory "testrunner_data"
eg: "require testrunner_data/file_1"

--------------------------------------------------------
The following languages are currently supported:
-Ruby
-Racket (cannot handle compilation errors)

